                <h1>Exploring the Art of Printmaking: Techniques & Trends</h1>
                <p>Printmaking is a captivating art form that involves transferring images from a matrix onto a surface, usually paper. Techniques like lithography, etching, and woodcut allow artists to create unique textures and layers. This medium has a rich history, allowing for both intricate designs and expressive styles in contemporary art.</p>
